<span class="narrator2">Aidan sits down, and places his hands underneath the desk. He fumbles with something in his pocket. (click:"pocket")[It starts beeping, and Aidan covers it up by coughing. 

The holographic poster behind Aidan plays a sequence of scenes.] (click: "scenes")[<br><br><div class="button5 centerAll">In one of them, a man with curly hair wears a black jacket. The material appears to be leather, so it must be a very old advertisement for something. The man leans against a four-wheeled vehicle, so yes, it is vintage. The vehicle emits a bright red light from the hood. The heading reads, "Knight Rider."<br><br>The next image</div> (click-replace:"The next image")[Two men in black suits pointing their guns at something or someone out of frame. They have funny haircuts. The title reads, "Pulp Fiction."<br><br>The next image (click-replace: "The next image")[Six youngsters with fluffy haircuts (lots of hairspray), wearing heavy makeup and baggy clothes. For some reason they smile a lot in front of a fountain. What's so fun about it? I don't know. All I know is they are friends.<br><br>The next image (click-replace:"The next image")[Close-up of a relaxed teenager, fingers laced behind his head, smiling at us. He seems to be extremely happy he had a day off. Day off from what? What's so horrible about what this boy does? Is Ferris Buller a slave? No clues are given.<br><br>The next image (click-replace: "The next image")[Six people, all half human, half screws are being bolted into the Earth by a hand coming from the sky, which holds a screwdriver. The hand is much bigger than the humans, so it'd be accurate to suggest that this is a metaphor of sorts. The title reads: "The Meaning of Life." However, no answers are provided.]]]]]

After he is done, he laces his fingers in a methodical way, sets his hands on top of the desk and looks at you. He's not drinking. For the first time, you see that a small chunk of his mustache is missing.</span>

"Tell me, do you have access to the top floors?"

<span class="narrator2">You do, but you shake your head.</span>

"I'm glad you like the <span class="toldYou popupLink">tea</span>. I don't trust anyone who doesn't drink in the morning."

<span class="narrator2">You take another sip to confirm it doesn't taste like Piste&#174; or cinnamon. The tea, or whatever this is, has a faint metallic taste.

Aidan pulls out a bottle from his desk. Inside the bottle, there's a plastic ring. He dips the ring inside the bottle, brings it to his mouth and starts making bubbles.

He sings one of Hiremy &amp; Hirschl's <span class="popupLink westHam">old jingles</span>:</span>

"I'm forever blowing bubbles,
pretty bubbles in the air,
they fly so high, nearly reach the sky
then like my dreams they fade and die."

